<section id="services-hero-532"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-4-3223cacf.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Built for Desert Pressure &amp; Soil.</span><h1 class="cs-title">Sprinkler System Installation in <span class="cs-color">Las Cruces, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Custom-zoned sprinkler systems sized to your home’s real water pressure, plant zones, and the city watering schedule. In-house crews, commercial-grade parts, and a controller that runs the right way the day we leave. 19 years in the Mesilla Valley. 500+ projects installed. Workmanship guarantee.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Get a Free Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><img alt="Lawn sprinkler and drip irrigation zone installed by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-drip-irrigation-ab8f5681.jpeg" height="660" width="480" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What You Get</span><h2 class="cs-title">Lawn Sprinkler System Installation, Engineered for the Desert</h2><p class="cs-text">A residential sprinkler system installation done right is more than buried pipe and a timer. It is a zone map matched to your water pressure, heads sized so every blade of grass gets the same water, and a controller programmed to the Las Cruces ordinance. We build in-ground sprinkler systems for full lawns, mixed turf-and-bed yards, and large lots across the Mesilla Valley.</p><ul class="cs-bullets"><li>Custom multi-zone design tuned to your house’s real PSI and gallons per minute.</li><li>Pop-up, rotary, and high-efficiency nozzles with matched precipitation rates.</li><li>Drip lines on dedicated zones for trees, shrubs, and xeriscape beds.</li><li>Smart wifi controllers that adjust to weather and follow city watering days.</li><li>Schedule-40 PVC, commercial-grade valves, and clean trenching that gets restored the same day.</li></ul><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule a Free Estimate</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/icon-irrigation-56.webp" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Pop-Up Spray Zones</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Low-profile pop-up heads for small turf areas, side yards, and parkways. Tight, even arcs with no overspray onto sidewalks.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Rotary Zones</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Long-throw rotor heads for larger lawns. Slower precipitation rates that soak in instead of running off our compacted desert soil.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Drip Zones for Beds</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Separate drip zones for trees, shrubs, and beds run off the same controller. Right water at root level, no waste, no leaf burn.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Smart Controllers</h3><p class="cs-item-text">WiFi controllers that auto-adjust to local weather and lock in your address-parity watering days. Phone control from anywhere.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-process-148"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> How We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Our 5-Step Sprinkler System Installation Process</h2></div><div class="cs-grid-wrap"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Free Site Visit</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We come out, walk the property, talk goals and budget, and look at existing turf, beds, and trees. Usually within a week.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Pressure &amp; Flow Test</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We test your hose-bib PSI, calculate gallons per minute, and check soil infiltration. Real numbers, not assumptions.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Zone Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We map every head, drip emitter, valve, and run-time on paper. Precipitation rates matched zone by zone. You approve before we dig.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Installation</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Our in-house crew trenches, lays pipe, sets heads and valves, mounts the controller, and restores all trenching same day. No subcontractors.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Programming &amp; Walkthrough</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We program your controller to the Las Cruces schedule, run every zone with you, and hand off a watering plan.</p></li></ul><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-3"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-4"></div></div></section><section id="services-signs-870"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Reasons to Install</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Las Cruces Homeowners Put In a Sprinkler System</h2><p class="cs-text">Most calls we get for sprinkler system installation start with one of these. A properly designed system fixes the underlying problem instead of patching it season after season.</p></div><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Tell Us About Your Yard</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div><ul class="cs-signs"><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Hand-Watering Is Eating Your Weekends</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Dragging a hose around a Las Cruces yard in July is a losing fight. A zoned system runs at dawn while you sleep and finishes before the city cutoff window starts.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Brown Spots, Burned Edges, Soggy Corners</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Old systems put unmatched heads on the same zone, so half the lawn drowns and half goes brown. We rebuild zones with matched precipitation rates so coverage is even.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Water Bills Climbing Every Summer</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A poorly designed sprinkler system can waste 30% or more of what you pay for. Smart controllers and right-sized zones typically cut outdoor water use 20% to 40%.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">New Build, Bare Dirt, No System</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Builders hand off a lot with a hose bib and a wave. We design a complete system before sod or beds go in, so the landscape settles in on the right water from day one.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Citation From the City</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Watering on the wrong day or between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. April through September draws warnings and fines. A controller programmed to your address parity stops that for good.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Adding Trees, Beds, or a Lawn Renovation</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">New plantings need their own drip zones. We can add a single drip zone to an existing system or build the whole yard fresh, depending on what you have.</p></li></ul></div><img alt="Healthy lawn maintained by Brainard's Greenscapes residential sprinkler system in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-1-7be715f9.jpeg" height="1094" width="616" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-region-450"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What Goes In the Ground</span><h2 class="cs-title">Commercial-Grade Components on Every Sprinkler System</h2></div><div class="cs-body"><p class="cs-text">A sprinkler system is only as durable as the cheapest part in it. We spec the same heads, valves, and pipe on a $2,500 lawn job that we use on commercial work, because replacing a $4 valve five summers in is not actually saving anyone money.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Pop-up &amp; rotary heads:</strong> Hunter, Rain Bird, and Toro pop-up sprays for tight zones; rotor heads with adjustable arcs and matched precipitation nozzles for larger turf areas.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Drip emitters and tubing:</strong> pressure-compensating emitters, 1/2-inch poly mainline, and 1/4-inch distribution tubing. Filtered and pressure-regulated for desert water quality.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Valves &amp; manifolds:</strong> heavy-duty solenoid valves in inspection-friendly valve boxes. Threaded unions so a future repair takes minutes, not hours.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Pipe:</strong> schedule-40 PVC mainlines and laterals, sized to your home’s actual flow. Properly buried below freeze line for our occasional hard freezes.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Smart controllers:</strong> WiFi-enabled smart sprinkler controllers from Rachio, Hunter Hydrawise, or Rain Bird with WiFi modules. Weather-based scheduling, phone control, and EPA WaterSense certified models available.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Backflow protection:</strong> code-required backflow preventers installed and tagged. Keeps irrigation water out of your drinking lines, no exceptions.</p><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Build Your System</a></div><img alt="Healthy turf served by a commercial-grade sprinkler system from Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-2-187f3fe4.jpeg" height="919" width="440" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-why-353"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-10dc66d2.jpeg" height="1836" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Choose Us</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Las Cruces Trusts Brainard’s with Sprinkler System Installation</h2><p class="cs-intro">A sprinkler system that lasts is the product of three things: a real water audit, a thought-out zone design, and an in-house crew that puts in the time underground. Cutting any of the three is how a system ends up leaking by year three.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-22-f514f4bf.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-23-a66a9e5c.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">19 Years in the Mesilla Valley</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">500+ projects installed across Las Cruces, Mesilla, and the surrounding desert. We know the soils, the pressure ranges, and the HOA rules.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Ordinance-Aware by Default</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Controllers programmed to your address parity. No watering on Mondays, no run times in the 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. window in summer. You stay off the city’s waste hotline.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">In-House Crews, No Subcontractors</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Same company designs, installs, programs, and guarantees the work. One number to call if a head ever needs adjusting.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Trenching, fittings, and structural work carry a workmanship guarantee for as long as you own the home. Heads, valves, and controllers carry full manufacturer warranties.</p></li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-quote-button">Get a Free Estimate</a></div></section><section id="services-pricing-219"><div class="cs-container"><article class="cs-price-card"><h2 class="cs-price-title">Sprinkler System Installation Cost in Las Cruces</h2><span class="cs-price-label">Typical Range</span> <span class="cs-price-amount"><span class="cs-price-symbol">$</span>1,500–$8,000</span><p class="cs-price-text">Sprinkler system installation cost depends on yard size, number of zones, head type, and controller. A small one-zone drip addition starts near $1,500. A full residential sprinkler system installation for an average Las Cruces lot typically runs $2,500 to $5,000. Larger lots, harder soils, or premium smart controllers push closer to $7,000 to $8,000.</p><ul class="cs-price-bullets"><li>Free on-site estimate, always.</li><li>Itemized quote tied to your zone design. No ballparks.</li><li>Workmanship guarantee on every install.</li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-price-link">Request a Custom Quote <svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></a></article><article class="cs-diff-card"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-c56eac00.jpeg" height="605" width="572" loading="lazy"><h2 class="cs-diff-title">The Brainard’s Difference</h2><ul class="cs-diff-list"><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 V21"></path><path d="M8 8 H16"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Faith-Centered</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Honest pricing, clear communication, and follow-through. We do what we say. If we miss something, we fix it.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 L20 6 V12 C20 16.5 16.5 20 12 21 C7.5 20 4 16.5 4 12 V6 Z"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Trenching, pipe, and structural work backed for as long as you own the home. Plus full manufacturer warranties on every head, valve, and controller.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2 C8 2 5 5 5 9 C5 14 12 22 12 22 C12 22 19 14 19 9 C19 5 16 2 12 2 Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"></circle></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Locally Rooted</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">In-house designers and crews who know the soil, the pressure ranges, and the Las Cruces watering ordinance better than anyone.</p></div></li></ul></article></div></section><section id="services-local-360"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Built for the Ordinance</span><h2 class="cs-title">Programmed to the Las Cruces Watering Ordinance</h2><p class="cs-text">Every controller we install is wired to the city schedule before we leave the property.</p></div><ul class="cs-local-list"><li><strong>Address parity:</strong> even-numbered addresses water Tue / Thu / Sat. Odd-numbered addresses water Wed / Fri / Sun.</li><li><strong>No watering on Mondays.</strong> Every controller skips Monday by default.</li><li><strong>April 1–Sept 30:</strong> no watering between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. We schedule pre-dawn and post-dusk run times only.</li><li><strong>Cycle &amp; soak:</strong> long zones split into shorter cycles so water soaks in instead of running off our compacted desert soil.</li><li><strong>Seasonal adjustments:</strong> spring start-up, summer scaling, fall blowout, winter rain mode. We can do these for you or set them to auto.</li><li><strong>Water-waste hotline:</strong> the city accepts reports at 575-528-4444. A correctly programmed system keeps you off that radar.</li></ul><p class="cs-text cs-text-footer">Source: <a href="https://lascruces.gov/property/utilities/utility-services/water-conservation/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces Utilities Water Conservation Program</a>.</p></div></section><section id="service-areas-825"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><aside class="cs-info-card"><div class="cs-info-head"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <svg height="10" viewBox="0 0 48 10" width="48" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"><path d="M2 5 H42"></path><path d="M36 1 L42 5 L36 9"></path></svg> Where We Install</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces &amp; the Mesilla Valley</h2></div><div class="cs-info-body"><p class="cs-text">We install sprinkler systems throughout Las Cruces and the Mesilla Valley, roughly within 30 miles of our office.</p><ul class="cs-locations"><li><a href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Las Cruces, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/mesilla-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Mesilla, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/dona-ana-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Doña Ana, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sonoma-ranch-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Sonoma Ranch, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/picacho-hills-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Picacho Hills, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/east-mesa-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in East Mesa, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/anthony-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Anthony, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sunland-park-nm/">Sprinkler Systems in Sunland Park, NM</a></li></ul></div><img alt="Brainard's Greenscapes sprinkler system installation in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-24-220fba7b.jpeg" height="130" width="428" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-office"><h3 class="cs-office-heading">Our Office Location</h3><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brainard's+Greenscapes/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x3c69d063ef4f24?sa=X&amp;ved=1t:2428&amp;ictx=111" class="cs-office-address" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces, NM </a><span class="cs-office-underline" aria-hidden="true"></span> <a href="/service-areas/" class="cs-office-button">View All Service Areas</a></div></aside><div class="cs-map"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="934" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Las%20Cruces+NM&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Las Cruces, NM service area" width="960"></iframe></div></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-8329654d.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights