aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Sprinkler System Installation FAQs</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much is sprinkler system installation in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Sprinkler system installation cost depends on yard size, number of zones, water pressure, and head type. A small drip zone addition starts near $1,500. A full residential sprinkler system installation for an average Las Cruces yard typically runs $2,500 to $5,000. Larger lots, harder soils, and premium smart controllers push closer to $7,000. Every job gets a free on-site estimate and an itemized quote before any digging starts.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How does a sprinkler system work?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>An automatic sprinkler system pulls water from your house line, splits it into zones at a manifold of electric valves, and pushes it through buried PVC or polyethylene pipe to pop-up or rotary heads. A controller opens one valve at a time on a schedule you set. Each zone is sized to your home’s water pressure and flow so every head delivers the right amount of water without dry spots or overspray.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long does a sprinkler system installation take?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Most residential lawn sprinkler system installations are finished in one to three days. A small one-zone drip addition can wrap in a day. A full multi-zone system on a half-acre lot is closer to three days, including trenching, pipe, valves, heads, controller, and cleanup. We restore all trenching the same day so your yard looks clean before the crew leaves.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How many zones does my yard need?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Zone count comes down to your home’s available gallons per minute and how many heads can run together without losing pressure. A typical Las Cruces home runs four to eight zones, splitting front lawn, back lawn, side yards, and any dedicated drip zones for trees and beds. We measure pressure and flow on site, then build the zone map around what your line can actually support.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Should I install drip or pop-up sprinklers?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Pop-up and rotary sprinklers are best for turf and broad ground cover. Drip is best for trees, shrubs, flower beds, and xeriscape plantings because it puts water at root level with very little evaporation. Most Las Cruces yards do best with both on separate zones so each plant type gets the right schedule and run time.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Will my new system meet the Las Cruces watering ordinance?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Las Cruces enforces a strict outdoor watering schedule by address parity (even addresses water Tue, Thu, Sat; odd addresses water Wed, Fri, Sun; no watering on Mondays; no watering between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. from April 1 to September 30). We program every controller to your address and the city schedule before we leave. You stay compliant from day one.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you offer sprinkler system blowout service for winter?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Las Cruces winters are mild, but a few hard freezes a year can crack pipes and split valves. We offer fall blowout, spring start-up, and seasonal controller adjustments so your system stays healthy year round. Existing-system clients can book recurring tune-ups, no install required.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Related Services</span><h2 class="cs-title">Pair Your Sprinkler System with These Services</h2><p class="cs-text">A sprinkler system works best as part of a complete plan. Most clients pair the install with one or more of these.</p></div><ul class="cs-related-list"><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/drip-irrigation/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Drip Irrigation</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Dedicated drip zones for trees, beds, and xeriscape plantings.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/smart-controllers/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Smart Controllers</h3><p class="cs-related-text">WiFi sprinkler controllers with weather-based scheduling and phone control.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/sprinkler-repair/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Sprinkler Repair</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Head, valve, and leak repair plus seasonal blowouts and tune-ups.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscaping</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Full landscape installation, sod, beds, and integrated hardscape.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscape-maintenance/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Ongoing care: pruning, drip checks, fertilization, and seasonal cleanup.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Ready for a System That Just Works?</h2><a href="/contact/" class="cs-talk-button">Get a Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
